caption: Good place for relaxing in Miami design district. The food is nothing special but it's expensive, probably because of the location.
Nice place for smoothies. Wish they had more wine and cocktail options.
Staff is super polite and the breakfast sandwich is incredible!

The service and quality in this cafe are so poor and unprofessional. They also have a bad hygiene when preparing food and drink orders. We ordered what was supposed to be green smoothies and something to eat - same lady that took our order and money at the register went to prepare the order with bare hands, which was so disgusting to see. And her customer service attitude was very rude! We’ve been here a couple of times but never going back after this episode.

Amazing place. I go 3-4 days a week to get my morning tea and breakfast and then I spend a few hours working. Everyone is so nice especially Peria and Alex. This place is highly recommend and be sure to try the breakfast sandwich.

Very good food and friendly service.The staff was extremely friendly, from the 1st day walked in by myself they made me feel right at home. Everything on the Menu and especially the Coffee is always well made. Would highly recommend to anyone .
Very bad experience. Forget the place. Service full of attitude, lot of food not available, no atmosphere.
Good coffee and friendly staff! Definitely a good place to go
They might be good for drinks, but dont order food. Not worth it$. Had breakfast and It was served in plastic containers, and the higiene was not that great.

Cute cafe that serves Panther Coffee.

Good place, it's chill, it has a comfortable outside sitting. Good location. There's shade if you're outside. The sun won't hit you in the face.  The food is good. I enjoyed coming here. Just a little bit pricey.
Most underwhelming spritz, valued at 10$. Tastes worst than it looks.
Good coffee. Nice location.
Very nice and chill environment. They let me relax with a cup of water on a hot morning. Friendly and nice staff.
you can take a rest while having a coffee inside the store that make you feel cool.

(Translated by Google) Beautiful bar for breakfast in the heart of the art district, its beauty is the outdoor area with its tables and chairs that dominate the whole square. The menu is varied and for all tastes the coffee (Panter Coffe roasting) is commendable. Helpful and fast staff. Great!
Had tea and coffee...
Delicious food for breakfast, healthy options, pricey. Great location and friendly staff. The avocado toast was delicious.
Great
We enjoyed our stop for coffee while visiting the area.
Avacado toast was very tasty. Service was good and quick. The scrambled eggs were not bad either but the avacado toast served all day was amazing  thank you guys.
Love the service, sit down outside atmosphere and good coffee
Excellent breakfast with high quality products. Thefood is delicious and fresh. Atmosphere is relaxedand cozy. And they have good coffee. Only minus are their plastic cups.
I work in the Design District and Ella Pop Cafe is hands down my favorite place to go around here to eat! Their service and food is perfect- totally reccomend it!
Adorable place

Excellent experience.. from walking in the door and being greeted by employee, seated and drink order taken. Excellent menu, excellent taste especially my special coffee. The team is very friendly and helpful.
Best service at the Design District 🤪 Always welcoming with a sincere smile !😃 Healthy menu as well Totally recommend this nice cafe shop
Love the food and service.

Visited here and got an iced coffee along with a muffin, and I must say that both treats were delicious! The coffee was the perfect blend of coffee, cream, sugar and syrup, and the muffin was sizable, moist and delectable. Also, the staff were quick to prepare these treats and ensured that they were prepared to my satisfaction. I enjoyed my time at Ella and will surely re-visit there when I’m back in Miami.
Very bad service, the employee making always mistake, working extremely SLOW,  tuna salad was spoiled . I think people shouldn’t  spend money for bad service and spoiled  food.

I had a breakfast sandwich on an everything bagel, an ice coffee and a nutter butter and absolutely loved them all. Although the morning was a bit busy, the staff was pretty quick in preparing the customers' orders. The customer service was on point! I'll definitely be returning when I'm back I'm Miami
Love this spot for lunch.. Their salads are very good and they also have amazing pastries !! Definetely look it up !
Had a ricotta toast with tea. It was quite good and big size. Bread is good, cheese and jam. It would be ideal to have proper plates and cups when eating in the place, too much waste.
Ok coffee, a fantastic blueberry pastry

Beautiful view for people watching, friendly staff, I wish I would have got the pastries or healthy snacks, they looked amazing - this review is just for the drinks - terrible 😢 - espresso was super bitter and the matcha tasted weird (maybe it was because they were out of soy and substituted almond?)  I would go again and skip coffee/matcha drinks and try a pastry.
Cute spot with great outdoor seating. Avocado toast was fresh and delicious.
Yum
Beautiful little coffee shop with amazing coffee and pastries. Overlooked by many but is actually good . Service is great with friendly customer service .
Beautiful and quaint cafe in the Design District. The everything bagel was, well everything! - @miamiwellnessclub

Love the food here especially for lunch! And the pastries are amazing! The outdoor seating area is lovely. Also I love coming by when Michelle is working she's great at giving recommendations if you have food allergies and always welcoming. Both her and Ashley always have a such a positive attitude. I always leave feeling satisfied.

Fresh food, friendly service and a peaceful place to sit or quick on take-out. Home made soups, salads and sandwiches from quality ingredients. Breakfast, lunch, snack or early dinner. Pastry, muffins, donuts and other sweet treats. No longer a pop-up, Ella stands on its own and always does it right.

I am a fan of Michael Scharwtz and have always kept Michael's Genuine in my list of top 20 restaurants, unfortunately like many other Miami restaurants, Michael's didn't keep up over the years and this pop up cafe is another disappointment. Service is SUPER SLOW. Everyone inside was upset and only waited because they had already paid. There is nothing really interesting in the menu, only overpriced everything bagel and cookies. Avocado toast was OK... but who can ruin an avocado toast. I left the cafe smelling like a kitchen, hungry and dissatisfied. Thumbs down!!!

I was there yesterday and loved my cappuccino. Staff was awesome, forgot the name of my server but she made me amazing coffee. I also had the most freshest and moist donut ever. I generally don't like donuts, this one was amazing though. Highly recommend it.
I love this place. The staff is friendly and the food (avocado toast) is always perfect! With a hefty serving too.
They serve local Panther coffee and it tastes amazing. Pair it with one of their decadent donut and voilà!

Cute place to have a delicious lunch in Design District! I had the turkey sandwich and the mayo in there tasted like HEAVEN! Plus, staff were very welcoming and brought my plate while I was seating outside on the terrace. Definitely comming back to try their pastries too. See you soon!
I went to Ella for coffee and it was alright.  A bit pricey but good quality coffee.  The seating area outside makes it a nice place to hang out.

Unprofessional. Incompetent. Waited in tiny line fifteen minutes for slow service only to be told half an hour before closing that they weren't serving food, even though they were making food right I front of me and serving it.

It was absolutely horrible. There were bugs all over the cookies, donuts, and pastries in the front. The milk to mix my coffee was warm and had been out all day, the service sucked. Point blank, over priced food for stale cookies, crappy service, and milk that will make you sick. DO NOT GO WASTE YOUR TIME OR MONEY.
Overpriced
Very hard to find seat here.   Good milk option for coffee and cute space and they put pretty Xmas decor up (December).  Good place to get a quick bite and to rest your feet from too much shopping.

Ella is the worst restaurant in Miami. I ordered a salad and all the greens were rotten and the servers didn't do anything when i show them the plate. On top of that is overpriced and they didn't return my  money. I would never recommend this place...cause it's definitely disgusting!!!
These people are very great and really good in customer service especially a French sweet lady that always smiling and ready to take your Oder,the best place to get your coffe.👍

(Original) Perché ci sono delle Ragazze cordiali,  gentili e professionali. Inoltre, hanno un sorriso contagioso......senza contare dei loro prodotti di ottima qualità. Da ritornare!!!!
Food was Disappointing and I spent $40. Coffee was ok, dessert excellent. You guys should sell food here but just coffee and pastries. I was expecting a lot since I am a fan of Michael Schwartz
Coffee is not good at all and pricey.

Disappointed. Don't have donuts on a Sunday??? That's just sad. Also, gluten free bread is available upon request...but if they don't like the flavor pairing, they simply won't do it gluten free, so never mind your food allergies. The summer roll has an overwhelming amount of shrimp. The turkey sandwich was good, as was the cookie and lemonade.
Seriously $5 for a not very good 12oz drip coffee is just offensive. Not a pour over just something they get from a flask
